  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Primary Objective is to evaluate the influence of psychosocial interventions in the treatment
      of children and adolescents with type 1 diabetes mellitus by measuring the connection between
      these interventions to quality of life and to metabolic control. Secondary Objective is to
      provide an opportunity, through quality of life (QOL) questionnaires, for enhanced
      communication between the patient, family and diabetes care team and also an opportunity to
      resolve negative issues.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
